Finance Accounting Manager - PT Shriram Seed Indonesia
Finance Accounting Manager  -
Finance Accounting Manager
Responsibilities
Generally responsible for  managing all finance and accounting units of the Company , Establishes financial status by developing and implementing systems for collecting, analyzing, verifying, and reporting financial information; managing staff Build and manages a highly motivated team of professionalsCo-coordinating with all external agencies, consultants & Head office.Achieves accounting operational objectives by contributing accounting information and recommendations to strategic plans and reviews; preparing and completing action plans; implementing production, productivity, quality, and customer-service standards; resolving problems; completing audits; identifying trends; determining system improvements; implementing change.Meets accounting financial objectives by forecasting requirements; preparing an annual budget; scheduling expenditures; analyzing variances; initiating corrective actions.Confirms financial status by monitoring revenue and expenses; coordinating the collection, consolidation, and evaluation of financial data; preparing special reports.Maintains accounting controls by establishing a chart of accounts; defining accounting policies and procedures.Guides other departments by researching and interpreting accounting policy; applying observations and recommendations to operational issues.Maintains financial security by establishing internal controls.Avoids legal challenges by understanding current and proposed legislation; enforcing accounting regulations; recommending new procedures.Protects organization's value by keeping information confidential.Ensures all reporting & MISMonitors sales, receivables ,inventory & working capitalMonitors purchases, payables & other disbursement activitiesEnsure corporate compliance Requirements: Possess at least Bachelor Degree in Accounting from reputable university & CPAAt least 5 year(s) working experience at Finance managerHaving experience as external auditor in big-four public accounting firm will be an advantageExcellence knowledge of finance, accounting, tax, budgeting, risk and complianceStrong interpersonal skills, communication and good analytical skillsProficient in written and oral in EnglishPossess good computer skills
